Most Support U.S. Guarantee of Health Plans

A majority of Americans say the federal government should guarantee health insurance to every American, especially children, and are willing to pay higher taxes to do it, according to the latest New York Times/CBS News Poll. In the poll, Americans showed a striking willingness to make tradeoffs for a better health care system, including paying as much as $500 more in taxes a year and forgoing future tax cuts.

